1379
01:20:23.460 --> 01:20:27.220
When we look into the pathophysiology of the primary HHH, we can see

1380
01:20:27.280 --> 01:20:31.100
that when there's a trigger, like a virus, the dendritic cells

1381
01:20:31.120 --> 01:20:35.080
process the peptide and present the peptide to the CD8+ cytotoxic

1382
01:20:35.120 --> 01:20:38.960
T cells. And CD8+ T cell expansion leads

1383
01:20:39.020 --> 01:20:40.500
to secretion of interferon gamma.

1384
01:20:40.960 --> 01:20:43.200
However, because of the cytotoxic defect,

1385
01:20:44.120 --> 01:20:48.060
dendritic cells are not cleared, and sustained dendritic cell presentation

1386
01:20:48.100 --> 01:20:51.880
of the peptide leads to the extensive expansion of the CD8 T

1387
01:20:51.960 --> 01:20:55.620
cell with the interferon gamma secretion, leading to the macrophage

1388
01:20:55.660 --> 01:20:59.600
activation and the cytokine storm, and finally, the systemic symptoms

1389
01:20:59.660 --> 01:21:03.230
like fever, cytopenia, or hepatosplenomegaly, and

1390
01:21:03.240 --> 01:21:07.100
hemophagocytosis. This is the pathophysiology of the primary

1391
01:21:07.260 --> 01:21:11.040
HHH. However, the pathophysiology of the secondary

1392
01:21:11.220 --> 01:21:14.570
HHH is not clear, although they share the

1393
01:21:15.100 --> 01:21:18.520
common name and although the secondary HHH

1394
01:21:18.800 --> 01:21:22.590
diagnosed criteria is mostly derived from the primary HHH.

1395
01:21:23.440 --> 01:21:27.100
So our key question was, what is the immunopathology

1396
01:21:27.200 --> 01:21:31.060
underlying the secondary HHH, especially with the lymphoma-associated

